{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1841,"text":"So I thought I'd talk about identity."},{"time":3627,"text":"That's sort of an interesting\nenough topic to me."},{"time":6060,"text":"And the reason was,\nbecause when I was asked to do this,"},{"time":9238,"text":"I'd just read, in one of the papers,\nI can't remember,"},{"time":12801,"text":"something from someone at Facebook\nsaying, well,"},{"time":16204,"text":"\"we need to make everybody\nuse their real names.\""},{"time":17844,"text":"and then that's basically\nall the problems solved."},{"time":20202,"text":"And that's so wrong,"},{"time":22147,"text":"that's such a fundamentally,\nreactionary view of identity,"},{"time":26090,"text":"and it's going to get us\ninto all sorts of trouble."},{"time":28495,"text":"And so what I thought I'd do"},{"time":29853,"text":"is I'll explain four\nsort of problems about it,"},{"time":33858,"text":"and then I'll suggest a solution,"},{"time":35821,"text":"which hopefully you\nmight find interesting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37893,"text":"So just to frame the problem,"},{"time":39944,"text":"what does authenticity mean?"},{"time":41534,"text":"That's me, that's\na camera phone picture of me"},{"time":46624,"text":"looking at a painting."},{"time":47604,"text":"[What's the Problem?]"},{"time":48369,"text":"That's a painting that was painted"},{"time":49501,"text":"by a very famous forger,"},{"time":51543,"text":"and because I'm not very good\nat presentations,"},{"time":53806,"text":"I already can't remember the name\nthat I wrote on my card."},{"time":56545,"text":"And he was incarcerated\nin, I think, Wakefield Prison"},{"time":60423,"text":"for forging masterpieces by,\nI think, French Impressionists."},{"time":63989,"text":"And he's so good at it,\nthat when he was in prison,"},{"time":67168,"text":"everybody in prison,\nthe governor and whatever,"},{"time":68544,"text":"wanted him to paint masterpieces\nto put on the walls,"},{"time":71391,"text":"because they were so good."},{"time":72683,"text":"And so that's a masterpiece,"},{"time":74067,"text":"which is a fake of a masterpiece,"},{"time":76066,"text":"and bonded into the canvas is a chip\nwhich identifies that as a real fake,"},{"time":82729,"text":"if you see what I mean."},{"time":84261,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":85453,"text":"So when we're talking about authenticity,"},{"time":87696,"text":"it's a little more fractal than it appears\nand that's a good example to show it."},{"time":93158,"text":"I tried to pick four problems\nthat will frame the issue properly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":97139,"text":"So the first problem, I thought,"},{"time":98687,"text":"Chip and PIN, right?"},{"time":100239,"text":"[Banks and legacies\nbringing down the system from within]"},{"time":101753,"text":"[Offline solutions do not work online]"},{"time":102625,"text":"I'm guessing everyone's got\na chip and PIN card, right?"},{"time":105241,"text":"So why is that a good example?"},{"time":107007,"text":"That's the example of how\nlegacy thinking about identity"},{"time":110482,"text":"subverts the security\nof a well-constructed system."},{"time":113400,"text":"That chip and PIN card\nthat's in your pocket"},{"time":116191,"text":"has a little chip on it\nthat cost millions of pounds to develop,"},{"time":119433,"text":"is extremely secure,"},{"time":121010,"text":"you can put scanning\nelectron microscopes on it,"},{"time":123273,"text":"you can try and grind it down,\nblah blah blah."},{"time":125449,"text":"Those chips have never been broken,\nwhatever you read in the paper."},{"time":128938,"text":"And for a joke,\nwe take that super-secure chip"},{"time":132172,"text":"and we bond it to a trivially\ncounterfeitable magnetic stripe"},{"time":135686,"text":"and for very lazy criminals,\nwe still emboss the card."},{"time":139308,"text":"So if you're a criminal in a hurry\nand you need to copy someone's card,"},{"time":142815,"text":"you can just stick a piece of paper on it\nand rub a pencil over it"},{"time":145016,"text":"just to sort of speed things up."},{"time":146899,"text":"And even more amusingly,\nand on my debit card too,"},{"time":149995,"text":"we print the name and the SALT code\nand everything else on the front too."},{"time":152386,"text":"Why?"},{"time":155725,"text":"There is no earthly reason why your name\nis printed on a chip and PIN card."},{"time":159834,"text":"And if you think about it,"},{"time":161469,"text":"it's even more insidious and perverse\nthan it seems at first."},{"time":164587,"text":"Because the only people that benefit"},{"time":166401,"text":"from having the name\non the card are criminals."},{"time":168975,"text":"You know what your name is, right?"},{"time":170616,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":171517,"text":"And when you go into\na shop and buy something,"},{"time":173769,"text":"it's a PIN, he doesn't care\nwhat the name is."},{"time":176729,"text":"The only place where you ever have\nto write your name on the back"},{"time":179388,"text":"is in America at the moment."},{"time":180558,"text":"And whenever I go to America,"},{"time":181769,"text":"and I have to pay with a mag stripe\non the back of the card,"},{"time":183569,"text":"I always sign it Carlos Tethers anyway,"},{"time":185451,"text":"just as a security mechanism,"},{"time":187259,"text":"because if a transaction\never gets disputed,"},{"time":189497,"text":"and it comes back and it says Dave Birch,"},{"time":191474,"text":"I know it must have been a criminal,"},{"time":193213,"text":"because I would never sign it Dave Birch."},{"time":196048,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":197738,"text":"So if you drop your card in the street,"},{"time":199529,"text":"it means a criminal\ncan pick it up and read it."},{"time":201301,"text":"They know the name,"},{"time":202006,"text":"from the name they can find the address,"},{"time":203935,"text":"and then they can go off\nand buy stuff online."},{"time":206350,"text":"Why do we put the name on the card?"},{"time":208562,"text":"Because we think identity\nis something to do with names,"},{"time":212281,"text":"and because we're rooted\nin the idea of the identity card,"},{"time":215976,"text":"which obsesses us."},{"time":217092,"text":"And I know it crashed and burned\na couple of years ago,"},{"time":219688,"text":"but if you're someone in politics\nor the home office or whatever,"},{"time":224243,"text":"and you think about identity,"},{"time":225648,"text":"you can only think of identity\nin terms of cards with names on them."},{"time":228863,"text":"And that's very subversive\nin a modern world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232009,"text":"So the second example I thought I'd use"},{"time":234265,"text":"is chatrooms."},{"time":236331,"text":"[Chatrooms and Children]"},{"time":237135,"text":"I'm very proud of that picture,\nthat's my son"},{"time":239325,"text":"playing in his band with his friends\nfor the first-ever gig,"},{"time":243401,"text":"I believe you call it, where he got paid."},{"time":245370,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":246157,"text":"And I love that picture."},{"time":248035,"text":"I like the picture of him\ngetting into medical school a lot better,"},{"time":250801,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":251501,"text":"I like that picture for the moment."},{"time":253614,"text":"Why do I use that picture?"},{"time":254589,"text":"Because that was very interesting,\nwatching that experience as an old person."},{"time":259678,"text":"So him and his friends,"},{"time":261121,"text":"they get together, they booked a room,\nlike a church hall,"},{"time":263999,"text":"and they got all their friends\nwho had bands,"},{"time":265849,"text":"and they got them together,"},{"time":267159,"text":"and they do it all on Facebook,"},{"time":268660,"text":"and then they sell tickets,\nand the first band on the -"},{"time":272458,"text":"I was going to say \"menu,\""},{"time":273343,"text":"that's probably\nthe wrong word for it, isn't it?"},{"time":275653,"text":"The first band on the list of bands"},{"time":277583,"text":"that appears at some\npublic music performance of some kind"},{"time":282140,"text":"gets the sales from the first 20 tickets,"},{"time":284309,"text":"then the next band gets the next 20,"},{"time":286129,"text":"and so on."},{"time":287115,"text":"They were at the bottom of the menu,"},{"time":288451,"text":"they were like fifth,\nI thought they had no chance."},{"time":290569,"text":"He actually got 20 quid. Fantastic, right?"},{"time":292831,"text":"But my point is,\nthat all worked perfectly,"},{"time":294928,"text":"except on the web."},{"time":297709,"text":"So they're sitting on Facebook,"},{"time":299902,"text":"and they're sending these messages\nand arranging things"},{"time":302768,"text":"and they don't know who anybody is, right?"},{"time":305087,"text":"That's the big problem\nwe're trying to solve."},{"time":306718,"text":"If only they were using the real names,"},{"time":308685,"text":"Then you wouldn't be worried\nabout them on the Internet."},{"time":311376,"text":"And so when he says to me,"},{"time":312621,"text":"\"Oh, I want to go to a chatroom\nto talk about guitars\" or something,"},{"time":316987,"text":"I'm like, \"oh, well,\nI don't want you to go into a chatroom"},{"time":320236,"text":"to talk about guitars, because\nthey might not all be your friends,"},{"time":323594,"text":"and some of the people\nthat are in the chatroom"},{"time":325857,"text":"might be perverts and teachers\nand vicars.\""},{"time":329414,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":331239,"text":"I mean, they generally are,\nwhen you look in the paper, right?"},{"time":334168,"text":"So I want to know who\nall the people in the chatroom are."},{"time":337224,"text":"So okay, you can go in the chatroom,"},{"time":338963,"text":"but only if everybody in the chatroom\nis using their real names,"},{"time":341987,"text":"and they submit full copies\nof their police report."},{"time":346352,"text":"But of course, if anybody\nin the chatroom asked for his real name,"},{"time":349472,"text":"I'd say no.\nYou can't give them your real name."},{"time":351714,"text":"Because what happens\nif they turn out to be perverts,"},{"time":354414,"text":"and teachers and whatever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":357087,"text":"So you have this odd sort of paradox"},{"time":358826,"text":"where I'm happy for him\nto go into this space"},{"time":361157,"text":"if I know who everybody else is,"},{"time":363099,"text":"but I don't want anybody else\nto know who he is."},{"time":365462,"text":"And so you get\nthis sort of logjam around identity"},{"time":367638,"text":"where you want full disclosure\nfrom everybody else,"},{"time":369274,"text":"but not from yourself."},{"time":370569,"text":"And there's no progress, we get stuck."},{"time":372576,"text":"And so the chatroom thing\ndoesn't work properly,"},{"time":374886,"text":"and it's a very bad way\nof thinking about identity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379251,"text":"So on my RSS feed,\nI saw this thing about -"},{"time":382186,"text":"I just said something bad\nabout my RSS feed, didn't I?"},{"time":384782,"text":"I should stop saying it like that."},{"time":386537,"text":"For some random reason, I can't imagine,"},{"time":388070,"text":"something about cheerleaders\nturned up in my inbox."},{"time":390226,"text":"And I read this story about cheerleaders,"},{"time":392203,"text":"and it's a fascinating story."},{"time":393652,"text":"This happened a couple of years ago\nin the U.S."},{"time":395867,"text":"There were some cheerleaders\nin a team at a high school"},{"time":398592,"text":"in the U.S., and they said mean things"},{"time":401475,"text":"about their cheerleading coach,"},{"time":402661,"text":"as I'm sure kids do\nabout all of their teachers"},{"time":404872,"text":"all of the time,"},{"time":406199,"text":"and somehow the cheerleading coach\nfound out about this."},{"time":408279,"text":"She was very upset."},{"time":409743,"text":"And so she went to one of the girls,\nand said,"},{"time":411910,"text":"\"you have to give me\nyour Facebook password.\""},{"time":414030,"text":"I read this all the time,\nwhere even at some universities"},{"time":417719,"text":"and places of education,"},{"time":418619,"text":"kids are forced to hand over\ntheir Facebook passwords."},{"time":420348,"text":"So you've got to give them\nyour Facebook password."},{"time":423103,"text":"She was a kid!"},{"time":423976,"text":"What she should have said"},{"time":425162,"text":"is, \"my lawyer will be calling you"},{"time":426392,"text":"first thing in the morning."},{"time":427182,"text":"It's an outrageous imposition"},{"time":429303,"text":"on my 4th Amendment right to privacy,"},{"time":431162,"text":"and you're going to be sued"},{"time":431947,"text":"for all the money you've got.\""},{"time":432542,"text":"That's what she should have said."},{"time":433598,"text":"But she's a kid,"},{"time":434577,"text":"so she hands over the password."},{"time":436396,"text":"The teacher can't log into Facebook,"},{"time":438446,"text":"because the school\nhas blocked access to Facebook."},{"time":441618,"text":"So the teacher can't log into Facebook\nuntil she gets home."},{"time":443531,"text":"So the girl tells her friends,"},{"time":445229,"text":"guess what happened?"},{"time":445790,"text":"The teacher logged in, she knows."},{"time":447386,"text":"So the girls just all logged into Facebook\non their phones,"},{"time":449227,"text":"and deleted their profiles."},{"time":451094,"text":"And so when the teacher logged in,\nthere was nothing there."},{"time":453979,"text":"My point is, those identities,\nthey don't think about them the same way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459631,"text":"Identity is, especially when\nyou're a teenager, a fluid thing."},{"time":463360,"text":"You have lots of identities."},{"time":464965,"text":"And you can have an identity,\nyou don't like it,"},{"time":467215,"text":"because it's subverted in some way,\nor it's insecure, or it's inappropriate,"},{"time":470811,"text":"you just delete it and get another one."},{"time":472893,"text":"The idea that you have an identity\nthat's given to you by someone,"},{"time":476217,"text":"the government or whatever,"},{"time":477036,"text":"and you have to stick with that identity\nand use it in all places,"},{"time":479155,"text":"that's absolutely wrong."},{"time":480863,"text":"Why would you want to really know\nwho someone was on Facebook,"},{"time":483895,"text":"unless you wanted to abuse them\nand harass them in some way?"},{"time":486777,"text":"And it just doesn't work properly."},{"time":489408,"text":"And my fourth example is\nthere are some cases"},{"time":491622,"text":"where you really want to be -"},{"time":494055,"text":"In case you're wondering,\nthat's me at the G20 protest."},{"time":497625,"text":"I wasn't actually at the G20 protest,\nbut I had a meeting at a bank"},{"time":501301,"text":"on the day of the G20 protest,\nand I got an email from the bank"},{"time":504734,"text":"saying please don't wear a suit,\nbecause it'll inflame the protesters."},{"time":509295,"text":"I look pretty good in a suit, frankly,"},{"time":511069,"text":"so you can see why it would drive them"},{"time":512759,"text":"into an anti-capitalist frenzy."},{"time":514260,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":514795,"text":"So I thought, well, look."},{"time":515724,"text":"If I don't want to inflame the protesters,"},{"time":518893,"text":"the obvious thing to do"},{"time":519809,"text":"is go dressed as a protester."},{"time":521214,"text":"So I went dressed completely in black,"},{"time":523232,"text":"you know, with a black balaclava,"},{"time":525116,"text":"I had black gloves on,"},{"time":525950,"text":"but I've taken them off\nto sign the visitor's book."},{"time":527587,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":528159,"text":"I'm wearing black trousers, black boots,"},{"time":530342,"text":"I'm dressed completely in black."},{"time":531748,"text":"I go into the bank at 10 o'clock,"},{"time":532922,"text":"go, \"Hi, I'm Dave Birch,"},{"time":533887,"text":"I've got a 3 o'clock\nwith so and so there.\""},{"time":535163,"text":"Sure. They sign me in."},{"time":536604,"text":"There's my visitor's badge."},{"time":539375,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":540266,"text":"So this nonsense"},{"time":541584,"text":"about you've got to have real names\non Facebook and whatever,"},{"time":543638,"text":"that gets you that kind of security."},{"time":545873,"text":"That gets you security theater,\nwhere there's no actual security,"},{"time":550392,"text":"but people are sort of playing parts\nin a play about security."},{"time":553730,"text":"And as long as\neverybody learns their lines,"},{"time":554855,"text":"everyone's happy."},{"time":556391,"text":"But it's not real security."},{"time":559255,"text":"Especially because I hate banks\nmore than the G20 protesters do,"},{"time":562497,"text":"because I work for them."},{"time":563682,"text":"I know that things are actually worse\nthan these guys think."},{"time":566509,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":569872,"text":"But suppose I worked\nnext to somebody in a bank"},{"time":574966,"text":"who was doing something."},{"time":584744,"text":"Suppose I was sitting\nnext to a rogue trader,"},{"time":586934,"text":"and I want to report it\nto the boss of the bank."},{"time":589237,"text":"So I log on to do\na little bit of whistleblowing."},{"time":590653,"text":"I send a message,\nthis guy's a rogue trader."},{"time":593118,"text":"That message is meaningless"},{"time":594916,"text":"if you don't know\nthat I'm a trader at the bank."},{"time":597864,"text":"If that message just comes from anybody,"},{"time":599793,"text":"it has zero information value."},{"time":602450,"text":"There's no point in sending that message."},{"time":606463,"text":"But if I have to prove who I am,"},{"time":609230,"text":"I'll never send that message."},{"time":610635,"text":"It's just like the nurse in the hospital\nreporting the drunk surgeon."},{"time":614488,"text":"That message will only happen\nif I'm anonymous."},{"time":617409,"text":"So the system has to have ways\nof providing anonymity there,"},{"time":622200,"text":"otherwise we don't get\nwhere we want to get to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624463,"text":"So four issues.\nSo what are we going to do about it?"},{"time":627133,"text":"Well, what we tend to do about it"},{"time":631820,"text":"is we think about Orwell space."},{"time":634208,"text":"And we try to make electronic versions"},{"time":637354,"text":"of the identity card\nthat we got rid of in 1953."},{"time":639661,"text":"So we think if we had a card,"},{"time":642418,"text":"call it a Facebook login,"},{"time":643757,"text":"which proves who you are,"},{"time":645054,"text":"and I make you carry it all the time,"},{"time":646945,"text":"that solves the problem."},{"time":647763,"text":"And of course, for all those reasons\nI've just outlined,"},{"time":649921,"text":"it doesn't, and it might, actually,"},{"time":650913,"text":"make some problems worse."},{"time":651985,"text":"The more times you're forced\nto use your real identity,"},{"time":654808,"text":"certainly in transactional terms,"},{"time":657048,"text":"the more likely that identity\nis to get stolen and subverted."},{"time":659930,"text":"The goal is to stop people\nfrom using identity"},{"time":662194,"text":"in transactions which don't need identity,"},{"time":664371,"text":"which is actually almost all transactions."},{"time":666880,"text":"Almost all of the transactions you do"},{"time":669177,"text":"are not, who are you?"},{"time":670865,"text":"They're, are you allowed to drive the car,"},{"time":672999,"text":"are you allowed in the building,"},{"time":674547,"text":"are you over 18,"},{"time":675404,"text":"etcetera, etcetera."},{"time":677519,"text":"So my suggestion-I, like James,"},{"time":679350,"text":"think that there should be\na resurgence of interest in R &amp; D."}]},{"cues":[{"time":682511,"text":"I think this is a solvable problem."},{"time":683296,"text":"It's something we can do about."},{"time":685116,"text":"Naturally, in these circumstances,"},{"time":687064,"text":"I turn to Doctor Who."},{"time":688438,"text":"Because in this,"},{"time":690574,"text":"as in so many other walks of life,"},{"time":692218,"text":"Doctor Who has already shown\nus the answer."},{"time":695171,"text":"So I should say,"},{"time":695985,"text":"for some of our foreign visitors,"},{"time":698316,"text":"Doctor Who is the greatest\nliving scientist in England,"},{"time":702170,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":703747,"text":"and a beacon of truth and enlightenment\nto all of us."},{"time":706547,"text":"And this is Doctor Who\nwith his psychic paper."},{"time":710617,"text":"Come on, you guys must have seen\nDoctor Who's psychic paper."},{"time":712787,"text":"You're not nerds if you say yes."},{"time":714787,"text":"Who's seen Doctor Who's psychic paper?"},{"time":716923,"text":"Oh right, you were in the library\nthe whole time studying I guess."},{"time":719353,"text":"Is that what you're going to tell us?"},{"time":721423,"text":"Doctor Who's psychic paper"},{"time":722685,"text":"is when you hold up the psychic paper,"},{"time":724805,"text":"the person, in their brain,"},{"time":726343,"text":"sees the thing that they need to see."},{"time":728692,"text":"So I want to show you a British passport,"},{"time":731051,"text":"I hold up the psychic paper,"},{"time":732077,"text":"you see a British passport."},{"time":733557,"text":"I want to get into a party,"},{"time":735353,"text":"I hold up the psychic paper,"},{"time":736960,"text":"I show you a party invitation."},{"time":738413,"text":"You see what you want to see."},{"time":740488,"text":"So what I'm saying is we need\nto make an electronic version of that,"},{"time":743703,"text":"but with one tiny, tiny change,"},{"time":745900,"text":"which is that it'll only show you\nthe British passport"},{"time":748496,"text":"if I've actually got one."},{"time":749712,"text":"It'll only show you the party invitation"},{"time":750931,"text":"if I actually have one."},{"time":752328,"text":"It will only show you that I'm over 18\nif I actually am over 18."},{"time":755352,"text":"But nothing else."},{"time":757676,"text":"So you're the bouncer at the pub,\nyou need to know that I'm over 18,"},{"time":762451,"text":"instead of showing you my driving license,"},{"time":764475,"text":"which shows you I know how to drive,"},{"time":766316,"text":"what my name is, my address,\nall these kind of things,"},{"time":768912,"text":"I show you my psychic paper,"},{"time":770491,"text":"and all it tells you is\nam I over 18 or not."},{"time":773657,"text":"Right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775093,"text":"Is that just a pipe dream?"},{"time":776431,"text":"Of course not, otherwise\nI wouldn't be here talking to you."},{"time":778124,"text":"So in order to build that\nand make it work,"},{"time":781208,"text":"I'm only going to name these things,\nI'll not go into them,"},{"time":783979,"text":"we need a plan,"},{"time":785156,"text":"which is we're going to build this"},{"time":786405,"text":"as an infrastructure for everybody to use,"},{"time":788429,"text":"to solve all of these problems."},{"time":790283,"text":"We're going to make a utility,"},{"time":792331,"text":"the utility has to be universal,"},{"time":793879,"text":"you can use it everywhere,"},{"time":794762,"text":"I'm just giving you little flashes\nof the technology as we go along."},{"time":797977,"text":"That's a Japanese ATM,"},{"time":799360,"text":"the fingerprint template\nis stored inside the mobile phone."},{"time":802468,"text":"So when you want to draw money out,"},{"time":803455,"text":"you put the mobile phone on the ATM,"},{"time":804952,"text":"and touch your finger,"},{"time":806217,"text":"your fingerprint goes through\nto the phone,"},{"time":808289,"text":"the phone says yes, that's whoever,"},{"time":809980,"text":"and the ATM then gives you some money."},{"time":812184,"text":"It has to be a utility\nthat you can use everywhere."},{"time":815221,"text":"It has to be absolutely convenient,"},{"time":817007,"text":"that's me going into the pub."},{"time":820174,"text":"All the device on the door\nof the pub is allowed is,"},{"time":822967,"text":"is this person over 18\nand not barred from the pub?"},{"time":826640,"text":"And so the idea is,\nyou touch your ID card to the door,"},{"time":829970,"text":"and if I am allowed in,\nit shows my picture,"},{"time":831929,"text":"if I'm not allowed in,\nit shows a red cross."},{"time":833390,"text":"It doesn't disclose any other information."},{"time":835005,"text":"It has to have no special gadgets."},{"time":836917,"text":"That can only mean one thing,"},{"time":838552,"text":"following on from Ross's statement,"},{"time":840243,"text":"which I agree with completely."},{"time":841721,"text":"If it means no special gadgets,"},{"time":842833,"text":"it has to run on a mobile phone."},{"time":844207,"text":"That's the only choice we have,"},{"time":845310,"text":"we have to make it work on mobile phones."},{"time":847189,"text":"There are 6.6 billion"},{"time":848123,"text":"mobile phone subscriptions."},{"time":849047,"text":"My favorite statistic of all time,"},{"time":851083,"text":"only 4 billion toothbrushes in the world."},{"time":853060,"text":"That means something,"},{"time":854119,"text":"I don't know what."},{"time":855376,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":855754,"text":"I rely on our futurologists to tell me."},{"time":859217,"text":"It has to be a utility\nwhich is extensible."},{"time":860927,"text":"So it has to be something"},{"time":862212,"text":"that anybody could build on."},{"time":863802,"text":"Anybody should be able\nto use this infrastructure,"},{"time":865690,"text":"you don't need permissions,\nlicenses, whatever,"},{"time":868144,"text":"anyone should be able\nto write some code to do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":873176,"text":"You know what symmetry is,"},{"time":874441,"text":"so you don't need a picture of it."},{"time":876788,"text":"This is how we're going to do it."},{"time":877952,"text":"We're going to do it using phones,"},{"time":878986,"text":"and we're going to do it"},{"time":879612,"text":"using mobile proximity."},{"time":880768,"text":"I'm going to suggest to you"},{"time":881904,"text":"the technology to implement"},{"time":883240,"text":"Doctor Who's psychic paper"},{"time":884526,"text":"is already here, and if any of you"},{"time":886170,"text":"have got one of the new\nBarclay's debit cards"},{"time":888649,"text":"with the contactless interface on it,"},{"time":889878,"text":"you've already got that technology."},{"time":891569,"text":"If you've ever been up to the big city,"},{"time":893493,"text":"and used an Oyster card at all,"},{"time":894994,"text":"does that ring any bells to anybody?"},{"time":897089,"text":"The technology already exists."},{"time":897835,"text":"The first phones"},{"time":899225,"text":"that have the technology built in,"},{"time":899855,"text":"the Google Nexus, the S2,"},{"time":902154,"text":"the Samsung Wifi 7.9,"},{"time":902863,"text":"the first phones that have"},{"time":904355,"text":"the technology built into them"},{"time":905447,"text":"are already in the shops."},{"time":906281,"text":"So the idea that the gas man"},{"time":907993,"text":"can turn up at my mom's door"},{"time":910185,"text":"and he can show my mom his phone,"},{"time":912387,"text":"and she can tap it with her phone,"},{"time":913722,"text":"and it will come up with green\nif he really is from British Gas"},{"time":916029,"text":"and allowed in,"},{"time":917241,"text":"and it'll come up with red if he isn't,"},{"time":918911,"text":"end of story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":919521,"text":"We have the technology to do that."},{"time":921371,"text":"And what's more,"},{"time":922606,"text":"although some of those things\nsounded a bit counter-intuitive,"},{"time":924751,"text":"like proving I'm over 18\nwithout proving who I am,"},{"time":927539,"text":"the cryptography to do that\nnot only exists,"},{"time":929764,"text":"it's extremely well-known\nand well-understood."},{"time":931993,"text":"Digital signatures, the blinding\nof public key certificates,"},{"time":934648,"text":"these technologies have been around\nfor a while,"},{"time":936392,"text":"we've just had no way\nof packaging them up."},{"time":938464,"text":"So the technology already exists."},{"time":941181,"text":"We know it works,"},{"time":944869,"text":"There are a few examples\nof the technology being used"},{"time":946617,"text":"in experimental places."},{"time":948287,"text":"That's London Fashion Week,"},{"time":949615,"text":"where we built a system with O2,"},{"time":951489,"text":"that's for the Wireless Festival\nin Hyde Park,"},{"time":954256,"text":"you can see the persons"},{"time":955379,"text":"walking in with their VIP band,"},{"time":957140,"text":"it's just being checked"},{"time":957624,"text":"by the Nokia phone\nthat's reading the band."},{"time":958724,"text":"I'm only putting those up to show you"},{"time":960422,"text":"these things are prosaic,"},{"time":961651,"text":"this stuff works in these environments."},{"time":963533,"text":"They don't need to be special."}]},{"cues":[{"time":964986,"text":"So finally, I know that you can do this,"},{"time":971789,"text":"because if you saw\nthe episode of Doctor Who,"},{"time":974693,"text":"the Easter special of Doctor Who,"},{"time":976593,"text":"where he went to Mars in a bus,"},{"time":979969,"text":"I should say again\nfor our foreign students,"},{"time":981531,"text":"that doesn't happen every episode."},{"time":983204,"text":"This was a very special case."},{"time":984675,"text":"So in the episode where\nhe goes to Mars in a London bus,"},{"time":987916,"text":"I can't show you the clip,"},{"time":989589,"text":"due to the outrageous restrictions\nof Queen Anne-style copyright"},{"time":992613,"text":"by the BBC,"},{"time":994506,"text":"but in the episode\nwhere he goes to Mars in a London bus,"},{"time":997245,"text":"Doctor Who is clearly shown\ngetting on to the bus"},{"time":1001379,"text":"with the Oyster card reader"},{"time":1002679,"text":"using his psychic paper."},{"time":1004247,"text":"Which proves that psychic paper"},{"time":1006339,"text":"has an MSE interface."},{"time":1008054,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}